id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/costs-of-moving-house-in-turkey/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/costs-of-moving-house-in-turkey/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/costs-of-moving-home-and-dormitory-in-turkey.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/costs-of-moving-house-in-turkey/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<p class="wp-block-paragraph">How does the process work when you are not satisfied with your first dormitory or house? How much does it cost to move? In this article, we will take you step by step through what you need to know, the costs you may encounter and the important details you should pay attention to when moving house and dormitory in Turkey.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="house-and-dormitory-selection-in-turkey-what-to-consider">House and Dormitory Selection in Turkey: What to Consider</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Choosing a home is an important step for international students. Some key points to consider in this process are:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Budget:</strong> Your budget for accommodation will determine your choices. Dormitories are usually more affordable, but private apartments are also preferable.</li>



<li><strong>Location:</strong> Staying close to your university reduces transportation costs and saves time.</li>



<li><strong>Facilities:</strong> The facilities offered by the dormitory or house (internet, food, security, cleaning services, etc.) should also be taken into consideration when making a choice.</li>



<li><strong>Cultural Integration:</strong> Having international students living together in dormitories can facilitate social integration.</li>
</ul>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="the-house-rental-process-what-you-need-to-know-for-international-students">The House Rental Process: What You Need to Know for International Students</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The process of renting an apartment can present some challenges for international students. Here&#8217;s what you need to know in this process:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Rental Agreement:</strong> Before you rent, read the rental agreement carefully. It is important to understand the terms of the contract to avoid problems in the future.</li>



<li><strong>Deposit:</strong> A deposit is usually required from the tenant by the landlord. This amount is usually equal to one or two months&#8217; rent.</li>



<li><strong>Required Documents:</strong> Documents such as identity document, student certificate and income declaration are generally required for the rental process.</li>



<li><strong>Rent Cost:</strong> House rents in Turkey vary from city to city. For example, the monthly rent for an apartment in Istanbul can range between 75 &#8211; 250 USD, while in smaller cities it can be between 37.5 &#8211; 125 USD.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">You can also check out <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/"><span data-sheets-root="1">Dues and Apartment Expenses in Turkey: You can also take a look at What Does It Cover? </span></a>.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="advantages-and-disadvantages-of-changing-residence">Advantages and Disadvantages of Changing Residence</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Both accommodation options have their own advantages and disadvantages:</p>


<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th><strong>Kriter</strong></th>
<th><strong>Hostels</strong></th>
<th><strong>Houses</strong></th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><strong>Advantages</strong></td>
<td>&#8211; Cost effective. &#8211; Provides a social environment. &#8211; Provides services such as food, cleaning, security.</td>
<td>&#8211; It offers more freedom. &#8211; You can create your own living space.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Disadvantages</strong></td>
<td>&#8211; There may be restrictions on freedom. &#8211; Individual space may be limited.</td>
<td>&#8211; Rental costs are higher. &#8211; You are responsible for cleaning and maintenance.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="where-to-find-dormitory-and-home-opportunities-in-turkey">Where to Find Home and Dormitory Opportunities in Turkey</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">You can use a variety of resources to help you find housing and accommodation:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>University Offices:</strong> Most universities offer accommodation services for international students.</li>



<li><strong>Internet Sites:</strong> You can examine rental house advertisements on websites such as <a href="https://www.sahibinden.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Sahibinden.com</a>, <a data-wplink-edit="true" href="_wp_link_placeholder">Emlakjet.com</a>.</li>



<li><strong>Social Media Groups:</strong> You can get information about accommodation opportunities through student groups on Facebook and other social media platforms.</li>



<li><strong>Local Agents:</strong> Local real estate agencies can help you find reliable accommodation options.</li>
</ul>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="simplify-the-moving-process-enjoy-a-comfortable-life">Simplify the Moving Process, Enjoy a Comfortable Life!</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey is a country full of study and accommodation opportunities for international students. The process of changing dormitories and houses requires careful planning and research. You can choose the most suitable option by considering factors such as your budget, location and facilities. Remember, every new experience makes you grow and gives you the opportunity to get to know different cultures.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="frequently-asked-questions">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-documents-are-required-when-renting-an-apartment">How much does it cost to relocate to Turkey?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The cost of relocating to Turkey varies greatly depending on your circumstances. Expenses can include shipping household items ($3,000-$10,000), flights ($500-$1,500 per ticket), and initial permits ($80-$200 per person).  You&#8217;ll also need to budget for a short-term rental while you settle in.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">How much money do you need to live comfortably in Turkey?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For a single person, a comfortable monthly budget can range from <strong>$1,200 to $2,000</strong>, while a family of four might need around <strong>$2,800 to $4,000</strong>. These figures can be lower in smaller cities and higher in metropolises like Istanbul. Rent is the biggest variable expense.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What is the living expense of students in Turkey?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Student living expenses in Turkey are relatively low compared to Western countries. On average, international students should budget between <strong>$400 and $650 per month</strong>, including accommodation, food, and transport. This amount is lower in cities like Eskişehir and Konya compared to Istanbul.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Why is Turkey so expensive in 2025?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey has experienced a significant increase in the cost of living due to a high inflation rate and the devaluation of the Turkish Lira.  While prices for local goods and services remain relatively low for those with foreign currency, the rising costs of imports and essentials have made life more expensive for residents.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-are-the-advantages-of-hostels">What are the advantages of hostels?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Affordable cost, social environment and services are among the advantages of dormitories</p>', "wp_published_at" = '2025-09-02T10:02:06Z', "wp_modified_at" = '2026-03-15T18:50:49Z', "featured_image" = '{"provider":"external","src":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/costs-of-moving-home-and-dormitory-in-turkey.webp","alt":"Student carrying boxes in a dormitory or apartment, preparing to move in Turkey","title":"costs-of-moving-home-and-dormitory-in-turkey"}' WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'costs-of-moving-house-in-turkey';
