<li><strong>Internet Sites:</strong> You can examine rental house advertisements on websites such as <a href="https://www.sahibinden.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Sahibinden.com</a>, <a data-wplink-edit="true" href="_wp_link_placeholder">Emlakjet.com</a>.</li>



<li><strong>Social Media Groups:</strong> You can get information about accommodation opportunities through student groups on Facebook and other social media platforms.</li>



<li><strong>Local Agents:</strong> Local real estate agencies can help you find reliable accommodation options.</li>
</ul>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="simplify-the-moving-process-enjoy-a-comfortable-life">Simplify the Moving Process, Enjoy a Comfortable Life!</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey is a country full of study and accommodation opportunities for international students. The process of changing dormitories and houses requires careful planning and research. You can choose the most suitable option by considering factors such as your budget, location and facilities. Remember, every new experience makes you grow and gives you the opportunity to get to know different cultures.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="frequently-asked-questions">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-documents-are-required-when-renting-an-apartment">How much does it cost to relocate to Turkey?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The cost of relocating to Turkey varies greatly depending on your circumstances. Expenses can include shipping household items ($3,000-$10,000), flights ($500-$1,500 per ticket), and initial permits ($80-$200 per person).  You&#8217;ll also need to budget for a short-term rental while you settle in.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">How much money do you need to live comfortably in Turkey?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For a single person, a comfortable monthly budget can range from <strong>$1,200 to $2,000</strong>, while a family of four might need around <strong>$2,800 to $4,000</strong>. These figures can be lower in smaller cities and higher in metropolises like Istanbul. Rent is the biggest variable expense.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What is the living expense of students in Turkey?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Student living expenses in Turkey are relatively low compared to Western countries. On average, international students should budget between <strong>$400 and $650 per month</strong>, including accommodation, food, and transport. This amount is lower in cities like Eskişehir and Konya compared to Istanbul.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Why is Turkey so expensive in 2025?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey has experienced a significant increase in the cost of living due to a high inflation rate and the devaluation of the Turkish Lira.  While prices for local goods and services remain relatively low for those with foreign currency, the rising costs of imports and essentials have made life more expensive for residents.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-are-the-advantages-of-hostels">What are the advantages of hostels?</h3>



